html_file_warning: The infectiousDisease.latentPeriod.timeStepValue is used to create a shifted Weibull distribution and used as the "days_latent[0]" parameter in FRED.  The mean of the fitted Weibull distribution is 1.984, the gamma parameter is 2.2126752, the lambda parameter is 1.67, the shift is 0.5 and the threshold is 0.05.

The infectiousDisease.infectiousPeriod.timeStepValue is used to create a shifted Weibull distribution and used as the "days_infectious[0]" parameter in FRED.  The mean of the fitted Weibull distribution is 4.4, the gamma parameter is 2.378084, the lambda parameter is 2.405191, the shift is 2.0 and the threshold is 0.05.

The infectiousDisease.infectiousPeriod.timeStepValue is used to create a shifted Weibull distribution and used as the "days_symptomatic[0]" parameter in FRED.  The mean of the fitted Weibull distribution is 4.4, the gamma parameter is 2.378084, the lambda parameter is 2.405191, the shift is 2.0 and the threshold is 0.05.

The "exposed" value is the ratio of the fraction of exposed individuals over the fraction of sick individuals.  The "infectious" value is the ratio of the fraction of infectious individuals over the fraction of sick individuals.

To get FRED to behave as the Apollo parameters specify, we need to indicate to FRED that all vaccines are available on day 0.  We will restrict the administration of the vaccine in the "vaccination_capacity_file" parameter.

FRED requires a "constant" vaccine supply schedule, but allows us to restrict the capacity at which they are distributed.  Therefore we populate the file specified by "vaccination_capacity_file[0]" parameter with the vaccineSupplySchedule, and FRED assumes that there is always enough capacity to distribute the daily supply.  For FRED like we expect, we set the "vaccine_additional_per_day[0]" to indicate that every vaccine that will be delieverd available at time 0.

FRED requires that a contant number of antivirals become available each day. The supplySchedulePerDay for an antiviral treatment control strategy maps to FRED parameters "av_total_avail" and "av_additional_per_day"
